DISTRIBUTE
  Set a sector's distribution center for automatic commodity flow.

SYNTAX
  distribute <sects> [<x,y>]
  dist       <sects> [<x,y>]

DESCRIPTION
  Each sector has a distribution center.  During every update the
  distribution system moves commodities between a sector and its
  dist center based on each item's threshold (see info threshold).

  Sectors below threshold import from their dist center.
  Sectors above threshold export the surplus to their dist center.

  By default all sectors point to (0,0) — the capital.
  Change this to route commodities through a regional warehouse.

  The coordinate is relative to your own origin (0,0 = capital).
  Use '.' or 'h' to set a sector as its own distribution center.

  If <x,y> is omitted, displays current distribution center settings.

  <sects> accepts realm numbers (#N) and ?des=X designation filters.
  The ?des=X condition must be attached with no space: #2?des=m

EXAMPLE
  distribute * 0,0              reset all sectors to use capital
  distribute -4,2 -2,0          iron mine feeds to warehouse at -2,0
  distribute 5,-1 0,0           LCM factory distributes to capital
  distribute #1 4,6             point all realm 1 sectors to warehouse
  distribute #2?des=m 2,8       realm 2 iron mines to eastern warehouse
  distribute *?des=w .          warehouses distribute to themselves

